olive oil
1 stalk celery
2 clove garlic
1 carrot
1 packet chicken breast
1 packet fusilli
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
½ packet cream
1 packet red pesto
1 bag parsley
1 sachet Aussie Spice Blend

• Boil the kettle. Finely chop celery and garlic. Grate the carrot.Cut chicken breast into 2cm chunks.
• Half-fill a large saucepan with boiling water, then add a pinch of salt.
• Cook fusilli in the boiling water, over high heat, until ‘al dente’, 12 minutes.
• Reserve some pasta water (1/2 cup for 2 people / 1 cup for 4 people). Drain fusilli, then return to the saucepan.

• Meanwhile, heat a large frying pan over high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook chicken and celery, tossing, until browned, 4-5 minutes. Season with salt and pepper.
• Reduce heat to medium, then add carrot and cook, stirring, until softened, 3-4 minutes.

• Add garlic and Aussie spice blend and cook until fragrant, 1-2 minutes.
• Add chicken-style stock powder, cream (see ingredients) and some reserved pasta water (1/4 cup for 2 people / 1/2 cup for people), then cook, stirring, until slightly reduced, 1-2 minutes.
• Remove from heat, add fusilli and red pesto, then stir to combine. Season to taste.

• Divide creamy chicken and veggie fusilli between plates.
• Tear over parsley to serve. Enjoy!